DataElement.preferredName: Immature Granulocyte Increased Finding Yes No Indicator
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A yes/no indicator that describes whether or not immature granulocytes were found to be increased above normal.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A not-yet-mature white blood cell with staining granules in its cytoplasm. The staining granules may be neutrophilic, acidophilic, or basophilic in character. There are indications that an immature granulocyte count is a better measure of infection and sepsis than a total white blood cell count and comparable to absolute neutrophil count._A subjective response indicating that something is or was increased._Clinical, laboratory or molecular evidence, or absence of evidence of disease.
